⸻

Product Tagline

Realm

A world built for agents.

Compared to the previous VM-centric version, this one aligns much better with your startup reality:

* Realm V1 can be built mostly with Docker + Playwright.
* Pathway becomes immediately useful.
* Veil has a clear place in the architecture.
* Later, macOS Realm becomes just another execution engine, not the entire product.

That’s a much more defensible architecture because competitors can copy “AI + VM”, but it’s harder to copy a unified execution layer that can transparently switch between Browser, Container, VM, and Cloud realms.